name: Heartsaver® First Aid Student Workbook
description: The required student text for the classroom-based Heartsaver First Aid course. Full-color softcover, 88 pages, 8 1/2" x 11", plus the Heartsaver® First Aid Quick Reference Guide (90-1025). Based on 2010 American Heart Association Guidelines for CPR and ECC.

name: Heartsaver® CPR AED Student Workbook
description: The required student text for the classroom-based Heartsaver CPR AED course. Full-color softcover, 56 pages, 8 1/2" x 11", plus two CPR AED pocket reference cards (adult and child/infant). Based on 2010 American Heart Association Guidelines for CPR and ECC.

name: Heartsaver® First Aid CPR AED Student Workbook
description: The required student text for the classroom-based Heartsaver First Aid CPR AED course. Full-color softcover, 136 pages, 8 1/2" x 11", plus two CPR AED pocket reference cards (adult and child/infant) and the Heartsaver® First Aid Quick Reference Guide (90-1025). Based on 2010 American Heart Association Guidelines for CPR and ECC.

name: Heartsaver® First Aid CPR AED Instructor Manual
description: Provides information for teaching the Heartsaver® First Aid, Heartsaver® First Aid CPR AED, and Heartsaver® CPR AED courses. 122 full-color pages (including lesson maps), plus 6 page-divider tabs, 8 1/2" x 11". Formatted as a loose-leaf, 3-hole-punched manual that fits into a binder or the AHA Instructor Portfolio (80-1017), and includes an instructor CD. Based on 2010 American Heart Association Guidelines for CPR and ECC. NOTE: This manual does not cover Heartsaver CPR in Schools, Heartsaver Pediatric First Aid, Family & Friends CPR, or Family & Friends First Aid for Children

name: Heartsaver® First Aid CPR AED DVD Set
description: This 2-disc set includes the required practice-while-watching video segments for the Heartsaver® First Aid, Heartsaver® First Aid CPR AED, and Heartsaver® CPR AED courses. Running times: First aid DVD: 112 minutes; CPR AED DVD: 77 minutes. Closed-captioned. Based on 2010 American Heart Association Guidelines for CPR and ECC

name: BLS For Healthcare Providers Student Workbook
description:
The required student text for the classroom-based Basic Life Support (BLS) for Healthcare Providers course and renewal course. Full-color softcover, 68 pages, 8 1/2" x 11", plus a pocket reference card, softcover book. Based on 2010 American Heart Association Guidelines for CPR and ECC. 
 
Manual includes information on:

single-rescuer and team basic life support skills for application in both in- hospital and out-of-hospital settings 
emergency recognition 
adult, child, and infant rescue techniques 
high-quality CPR 
AED use 
relief of choking.

name: BLS For Healthcare Providers Instructor Package
description:
Includes:
BLS For Healthcare Providers Instruction Manual
BLS For Healthcare Providers Student Manual
BLS for Healthcare Providers Course and Renewal Course DVD
American Heart Association Stopwatch

name: Prestan Infant CPR Manikin With Monitor
description:
Realistic to the eye and the touch, the Prestan CPR Infant Manikin is unlike any other on the market. Prestan manikins are uniquely designed as a clamshell that accommodates an easy-to-insert face-shield/lung-bag.  And with our patented face/head tilt, the Prestan CPR Infant Manikin simulates the way an actual victim's head would move if he required CPR.  In addition, the unique construction of our manikins incorporates a mechanism to help them use the correct force to compress the chest to the correct depth.
 
Prestan's revolutionary new CPR Rate Monitor allows for instant feedback to both instructor and student regarding the rate of chest compression. This allows each student to gauge their rate of compressions on their own as well as allowing the instructor to monitor several students quickly and easily.

name: Prestan AED Training
description: This flexible, realistic trainer prepares students to operate a variety of different AEDs in the event of a sudden cardiac arrest. Features a replaceable scenario/language module for easy upgrade anytime AED protocols are updated, five preprogrammed scenarios, clear voice prompts, built-in English and Spanish options, a metronome, and a pad sensing system that detects when pads are attached to a manikin. Compatible with any type of CPR manikin that is intended for AED training.
